Please contact us if you have any questions, comments or suggestions relating to this Policy.
Minute Website and End User Privacy Notice
Minute Spoteam Ltd. (“
we
“, “
us
“, “
our
” or “
Minute
“) respects your right to privacy. Your ability to make informed choices about the use of your information is important to us. This Privacy Notice explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect information we receive from visitors to our website,
www.minute.ly
(“
Site
“). This Privacy Notice also explains your ability to control certain uses of the collected information. “
You
” means any adult visitor to our Site and/or any parent or guardian of any minor whom you allowed to visit such sites and for whom you will be held strictly responsible.
If you are an individual located in the European Union (“
EU Individual
“), some additional terms and rights may apply to you, as detailed herein. Minute is the data controller in respect of the processing of Personal Data (as defined below) of visitors to the Site, as outlined in this Privacy Notice. Our registered office is Soncino St 3, Tel Aviv-Yafo, Israel and our registration number is 515090652. When we process information of visitors to Customer Sites (as defined below) in the context of providing services to our Customers, the applicable Customer serves as a data controller with respect to such Personal Data and we serve as a data processor.
“
Personal Data
” means any information that refers, is related to, or is associated with an identified or identifiable individual or as otherwise may be defined by applicable law. This Privacy Notice details which Personal Data is collected by us in connection with provision of the Services.
If you are a visitor to the website of one of our Customers, please see the “Visitors to Customer Sites” section below.
