Visitors to Customer Sites
We collect and process certain Personal Data of individuals who visit the websites of our customers (“
Customers
” and “
Customer Sites
“, respectively). We collect and use this data solely for the purpose of providing services to our Customers, at their instruction, and on their behalf.
When we process information of visitors to Customer Sites the applicable Customer serves as a data controller with respect to such Personal Data and we act as a data processor on its behalf.
When you visit our Customers’ Sites, we automatically collect information about which pages, your computer, including non-Personal Data such as your operating system, Personal Data such as your IP address (which is not retained), your general location (city and country), your browsing history which will include the pages visited, which videos are watched, which teasers are clicked, what articles are read and usage information from the “video player” such as when the video was played/paused, volume control, and information regarding your viewing history on the Customer Site.
The information we collect will be shared with the Customer whose Customer Site you visit.
In order to collect this information, we may place cookies on the Customer Site. Depending on the type of service we provide to the Customer, different cookies may be placed.
